div2.entryFree:

      لَبَّادٌ A maker, or manufacturer, of لِبْد [i. e.,
hair or wool commingled, and compacted together;
or felt]. (K.)


      مُلْقَحَةٌ A female camel that has her young one
in her belly: pl. مَلَاقِحُ: (S, K:) a pass. part. n.
from أَلْقَحَ. (Msb.)


      لَوْذَانِيَّةٌ, (as in some copies of the K,) or لَوَذَانِيَّةٌ,
(as in others and in the TA,) Circumvention;
delusion; syn. مُرَاوَغَةٌ. (K.) See 3.


      تَمْرٌ مُلَوَّزٌ Dates stuffed with لَوْز [or almonds];
(Sgh, K;) the stones being taken out and لَوْز put
in their place. (TA.)


      مِلْيَثٌ [accord. to the K and TA; but in the L,
↓ مليّث;] Strong; powerful: (K:) or very hard;
syn. شَدِيدُ العارضة. (L.)
